%h2
  Privacy Policy - For lawyers and nerds:

%p
  At NetworkMill, we collect and manage user data according to the following Privacy Policy, with the goal of incorporating our company values: transparency, accessibility, sanity, usability. This document is part of NetworkMill's Terms of Service, and by using NetworkMill.com (the “Website”), you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy and the Terms of Service. Please read the Terms of Service in their entirety, and refer to those for definitions and contacts.

%br
%h3
  Data Collected

%p
  We collect anonymous data from visitors of the Website to monitor traffic and fix bugs. For example, we may collect information like web requests, the data sent in response to such requests, the Internet Protocol address, the browser type, the browser language, and a timestamp for the request.

%p
  We ask you to log in and provide certain personal information (such as your name and email address) in order to be able to save your profile and contacts and comments associated with it.  In order to enable these or any other login-based features, we use cookies to store session information for your convenience. You can block or delete cookies and still be able to use NetworkMill, although if you do you will then be asked for your username and password every time you log in to the Website. In order to take advantage of certain features of the Website, you may also choose to provide us with other personal information, such as your picture or brief intro, but your decision to utilize these features and provide such data will always be voluntary.

%p
  You are able to view, change and remove your data associated with your profile. Should you choose to delete your account, please contact us at hi@NetworkMill.com and we will follow up with such request as soon as possible. You can also modify your notification preferences by clicking the appropriate link included in the footer of email notifications.

%br
%h3
  Use of the Data

%p
  We only use your personal information to provide you the NetworkMill services or to communicate with you about the services or the Website.

%p
  With respect to any contacts you may choose to add to NetworkMill, we take the privacy and confidentiality of such contacts seriously. We employ industry standard techniques to protect against unauthorized access of data about you that we store, including personal information. 

%p
  We do not share personal information you have provided to us without your consent, unless:

%ul
  %li
    doing so is appropriate to carry out one of your requests;
  %li
    we believe it's needed to enforce our Terms of Service, or that is legally required;
  %li
    we believe it's needed to detect, prevent or address fraud, security or technical issues;
  %li
    otherwise protect our property, legal rights, or that of others.

%p
  NetworkMill is operated from the United States.  If you are visiting the Website from outside the U.S., you agree to any processing of any personal information you provide us according to this policy.

%p
  NetworkMill may contact you, by email or other means. For example, NetworkMill may send you promotional emails relating to NetworkMill or communicate with you about your use of the NetworkMill website. NetworkMill may also use technology to alert us via a confirmation email when you open an email from us. If you do not want to receive email from NetworkMill, please opt out of receiving emails at the bottom of any NetworkMill emails.

%br
%h3
  Sharing of Data

%p
  We do NOT share your personal information with third parties. We currently use Google Analytics (traffic analysis, SEO optimization), Stripe (to process payments) and Mandrill (mailing list management). We listed below what data these third parties extract exactly. Feel free to check out their own Privacy Policies to find out more. 

%ul
  %li
    Google Analytics: anonymous (ad serving domains, browser type, demographics, language settings, page views, time/date), pseudonymous (IP address)
  %li
    Stripe: securely process your credit card payments; all information is kept strictly confidential.
  %li
    Mandrill: name and email of our beta subscription list.

%p
  We also use social buttons provided by services like Twitter, Google+, LinkedIn and Facebook. Your use of these third party services is entirely optional. We are not responsible for the privacy policies and/or practices of these third party services, and you are responsible for reading and understanding those third party services’ privacy policies.

%p
  We may choose to buy or sell assets. In these types of transactions, user information is typically one of the transferred business assets. Moreover, if we, or substantially all of our assets, were acquired, or if we go out of business or enter bankruptcy, user information would be one of the assets that is transferred or acquired by a third party. You acknowledge that such transfers may occur, and that any acquirer of us or our assets may continue to use your personal information as set forth in this policy.

%br
